The high novelty rate is particularly significant for the drug discovery pipeline envisioned in this thesis. A generative model that merely reproduces known structures would offer limited value for discovering novel absorbents. The ability to generate truly novel polymers, combined with the filtering and prediction stages described in subsequent chapters, enables a closed-loop workflow for computational polymer discovery.

