\section{Integration with the Discovery Pipeline}
\label{sec:pipeline_integration}

The generative model serves as the foundation of the broader computational pipeline developed in this thesis. Generated polymers enter a multi-stage filtering and evaluation process. First, validity checking ensures that only chemically valid structures proceed. Second, heuristic filters based on chemical properties (discussed in Chapter 6) eliminate structures that are unlikely to be effective absorbents. Third, for the most promising candidates, the predictive model estimates the expected absorption capacity against the target pharmaceutical. This integrated approach represents a shift from traditional trial-and-error laboratory synthesis toward a data-driven, computationally accelerated discovery workflow.
